# Human-Agent Ratio Improvement for Testers

A word on the streets is there's is a new metric in town: the Human-Agent Ratio. In this workshop, it is not about how many people's jobs we 
can delegate to agents, but on how many task-based agents we have captured and put to use to help us with our work. We seek efficiency and effectiveness equally, 
seeking to raise the bar in perspectives by capturing and sharing our ways of completing tasks with excellence. 

By taking Playwright Agents into use, you can already bring up human-agent ratio to 100%. Using all three out of the box with two pertaining to writing 
automation code, Your ratio would be 300%. I find myself currently in command of 20 something agents. 

As introduction to agents for testing, we build our own and share them around starting an open marketplace of ideas. Let's turn our personal human-agent -ratios away from the default of 0%. 
